summary: This is an automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system indicating that travel authorization 10892303-1 has been approved and is pending further approval. The trip is for a witness interview in California related to the case U.S. v. Epstein.

events.title: Witness Interview Travel Authorization
events.description: Travel authorization was approved for a trip to California for a witness interview related to U.S. v. Epstein.

keyFacts: A travel authorization (ID: 10892303-1) was approved by the DOJ for a trip to California related to the U.S. v. Epstein case.
The purpose of the trip was a witness interview, indicating ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case as of December 2019.
The travel dates were scheduled for December 15-18, 2019, and the authorization email was sent on December 20, 2019.
The document originates from the DOJ's internal E2 travel system, showing formal government procedures for case-related travel.
